<TEXT>
israeli soldiers fired into a crowd of 
rockthrowing youngsters at a gaza strip girls school monday 
killing a 15yearold palestinian according to arab reports 
officials at shifa hospital said asma abu obadah of the shati 
refugee camp died of a bullet wound to the head 
leaders of the yearold uprising in the occupied territories 
called for a week of strikes to mark thursdays first anniversary of 
the palestinian rebellion in the west bank and gaza 
they urged arab nations to reconsider their relations with 
the united states because of its refusal to give palestine 
liberation organization chief a visa to address the un general 
assembly 
arab reporters quoted witnesses as saying soldiers opened fire 
after dozens of students at the shati junior high school for girls 
threw stones at them 
officials of the un relief and works agency in gaza city which 
oversees aid for palestinian refugees confirmed the girl died of a 
bullet wound in the head but had no details 
at least 319 palestinians have been killed in the uprising and 11 
israelis also have been slain 
an 8yearold boy was wounded in the hip and back in 
confrontations thazt began in the refugee camp after the girls 
death said arab reporters and officials at the ahli arab hospital 
said 
three other palestinians all teenagers were reported wounded 
in the gaza strip 
about 100 palestinians demonstrated in the west bank city of 
ramallah 15 miles north of jerusalem israel television showed 
paratroopers shooting plastic bullets to dispersing the 
stonethrowing protesters and chasing youths into nearby houses 
also monday the army confirmed that palestinian prisoners held 
at the negev desert ketziot detention center held a hunger strike 
last week arab reports said the hunger strike was to protest prison 
conditions more than 2000 palestinians are believed to be held at 
ketziot 
the plobacked leaders in a leaflet marking the anniversary 
called the us decision to bar arafat a decision to silence the 
palestinian voice 
secretary of state george p shultz denied the visa on grounds 
arafat condones terrorism and the general assembly voted last 
friday to move its session to geneva so the plo leader can speak 
in the pamphlet the underground leaders called for strikes this 
week to mark the year of rebellion earlier they set a strike for 
tuesday to show solidarity with at least 5600 palestinian detainees 
in israeli jails 
judith green a member of a committee that aids palestinians in 
the west bank village of beita said she witnessed a rampage by 
israeli troops in the village on nov 19 
she told the associated press soldiers vandalized everything 
they passed 
they used rifle butts to smash windows they took large stones 
from terrace walls and threw them at cars windows shutters 
doors she said 
ms green a native of stuttgart ark who has dual usisraeli 
citizenship said villagers told her later a soldier killed a 
12yearold boy by shooting him in the head at pointblank range 
the army reported nov 23 that a 13yearold died of a bullet 
wound to the head after being a clash with soldiers nov 19 in beita 
an army spokeswoman said monday the death still was under 
investigation and refused comment on the charges of a rampage 
