a twoweekold strike by city employees of 
palermo has left the morgue full newborns unable to leave the 
hospital and traffic more hopeless than ever 
agony of palermo here its forbidden to be born or to die 
read the headline on the frontpage sunday of la repubblica a 
nationwide daily 
among the striking city employees were gravediggers traffic 
police school janitors and clerks in the office that gives out 
birth certificates 
italian news accounts said bodies in coffins were being stacked 
in the morgue during the strike 
