nations export revenue oil income this year will be 71 billion 
down from 91 billion in 1987 the plunge in oil prices since the 
early 1980s coupled with a foreign debt of 33 billion thwarted 
plans to expand and modernize the economy the oil crunch is also 
responsible for a sharp decline in the nations per capita income 
2782 in 1986 down from 3408 in 1980 
</TEXT>
