at the states only maximum security prison 25 miles south of salt 
lake city 
its a form of worship and i think prison officials really 
ought to be more cognizant of it as a rehabilitative tool said 
travis parashonts a paiute indian who is director of the utah 
office of indian affairs its a very uplifting and spiritual 
