<TEXT>
pioneer 12 was designed to orbit 
venus for just 243 days but it chalked up a solid decade of work 
monday amid raves from the scientists whove kept the project 
working 
the space probe has helped map 93 percent of venus searinghot 
surface while providing a new understanding of volcanics and land 
formation on earth 
it has sent scientists 10 trillion bits of data including 
information on the extreme greenhouse effect which appears to be 
trapping the suns heat and driving the planets surface temperature 
to 900 degrees fahrenheit 
it also has allowed them to speculate on the ways in which venus 
once thought to be the earths twin because of its similar size 
composition and the presence of continents mountains and canyons 
is different from our home planet 
we used to think when i was in school that venus and earth were 
twin planets said donald hunten a professor of planetary 
sciences at the university of arizonas lunar and planetary 
laboratory said at a meeting of scientists celebrating pioneers 
longevity more recently weve discovered they are really not 
very alike at all 
scientists at the meeting took the opportunity to call for a 
return to unmanned space probes in addition to the far more costly 
manned missions 
steven dorfman who works for hughes aircraft co a major 
government space contractor called for a return to a mix of small 
and large programs pointing out that the pioneer project was 
relatively cheap at less than 200 million in todays dollars 
dorfman said the united states launched 36 planetary launches in 
the 1960s but only 11 in the 1970s two are scheduled in this 
decade 
although venus has no oceans hunten said data suggests there may 
have been enough water vapor to form an ocean 4 billion years ago 
but high temperatures from the planets severe greenhouse 
effect in which clouds or pollution traps the suns heat near the 
planets surface may partially account for the differences between 
venus and earth he said 
additionally extreme stratospheric pollution on venus where 
chlorine is found at levels 100 to 1000 times the concentration 
found in the air above earth could further explain conditions on 
venus and provide a warning of our own future 
venus is not a living breathing example but a very dead 
example of what a polluted atmosphere is like said hunten adding 
that the pollution on venus is natural but the chemistry is the same 
as on earth 
lawrence colin pioneer venus project scientist said the 
anniversary is just a step along the way to many of us 
pioneers variable orbit which responds to the effect of solar 
gravity on venus has allowed the spacecraft to come as close as 93 
miles to venus and as distant as 1426 miles 
if plans are carried out on scheduled next year the magellan 
mission will team up with pioneer to provide high resolution radar 
mapping of venus surface in february 1990 pioneer will be joined 
by the galileo probe when it passes venus on its way to jupiter 
pioneer will continue to sample venus environment including 
monitoring an entire 11year sunspot cycle 
in late 1991 it will sample venus upper atmosphere in early 
1992 it will begin to burn its remaining fuel supply to maintain an 
orbit of 150 kilometers or lower if we can said colin 
when the fuel supply runs out estimated at some time late in 
1992 he added pioneer venus will meet a fiery death the end of 
the mission 
