<TEXT>
the general assembly on monday adopted a 
package of resolutions deploring south africas apartheid system 
and noted that japan is the leading trading partner of the minority 
whiteruled nation 
one resolution singled out israel and certain western states 
for criticism because of their continued military nuclear 
intelligence and technological trade and collaboration with south 
africa 
the general assembly passes similar antiapartheid resolutions 
every year 
by law and custom apartheid establishes a racially segregated 
society in which south africas 26 million blacks have no vote in 
national affairs the 5 million whites control the economy and 
maintain separate districts schools and health services 
the resolution condemning military collaboration with south 
africa passed 1232 with 29 abstentions israel which was 
criticized by name and the united states voted against it most 
western nations including australia and new zealand and japan 
abstained 
us delegate harvey nelson said the united states opposed the 
resolution because it explicitly criticized israel for actions 
which many have committed including some of those who protest most 
loudly 
another resolution calling on israel to end its collaboration 
with south africa particularly its longterm contracts for military 
supplies passed 10623 with 26 abstentions 
numerous western nations opposed that resolution because it 
singled out one nation for what they called unproductive criticism 
canada the united states and the 12 european community nations 
took that view 
the resolution calling for comprehensive and mandatory economic 
sanctions against south africa passed 12312 with 19 abstentions 
japan was mentioned in the text as south africas largest trade 
partner 
japanese ambassador hideo kagami contended the resolution gave 
the false impression that japan has been increasing its trade with 
south africa 
he said japanese trade as measured in yen had declined every year 
since 1984 a rise in trade as measured in dollars merely reflected 
the fall of the dollar against the yen he said 
that resolution called for the security council to make economic 
sanctions mandantory and appealed to britain and the united states 
not to continue using their veto power to block enforced sanctions 
the 12 opposition votes were from western europe canada japan 
and israel 
a resolution expressing international solidarity with the 
liberation struggle against south africa passed 1313 with 21 
abstentions by most of the western allies the united states 
britain and portugal voted against the measure 
the resolution called for full support for the african national 
congress the black guerrilla group fighting the south african 
government and affirmed the right to used armed struggle in pursuit 
of liberation 
portugals secondranking diplomat jose caetano da costa 
pereira said his country opposed apartheid but could not support 
the endorsement of armed struggle 
a resolution calling for voluntary international coordination and 
monitoring of boycotts against south africa passed 1364 with 14 
abstentions by western nations japan and malawi 
west germany portugal britain and the united states opposed the 
resolution which calls for nations to adopt voluntary sanctions 
against south africa preventing trade in nuclear materials and 
technology oil and petroleum credit and loans air transport and 
links culture and sports and military goods and services 
the current voluntary oil embargo against south africa would be 
made mandatory by the security council under a resolution that 
passed 1382 with 14 abstentions by western europe canada japan 
botswana lesotho and swaziland 
britain and the united states voted no and have vetoed 
attempts in previous years to make the embargo mandatory by using 
their veto in the security council 
