<TEXT>
ptl founder jim bakker forced to quit his 
multimilliondollar television ministry after admitting a sexual 
encounter with a church secretary was indicted monday along with 
three former aides on charges of fraud and tax evasion 
a federal grand jury charged bakker 48 and former aide richard 
dortch 57 in a 24count indictment with mail fraud wire fraud and 
conspiring to defraud the public through the sale of lifetime 
partnerships in the ministrys heritage village theme park in fort 
mill sc south of charlotte 
if convicted they could face up to five years in prison and 
250000 fines on each count 
bakkers wife tammy also a target of the grand jury was not 
indicted 
a second 11count indictment charged david taggart and his 
brother james with tax evasion and conspiracy to impede the 
internal revenue service in the collection of taxes david taggart 
is former ptl vice president and special assistant to bakker james 
is a former interior designer for ptl 
