editors note soap operas are not known for heavy social 
philosophy or ethnic diversity so it was unusual to say the least 
for two orthodox jews to make an appearance on nbcs day of our 
lives the explanation is leah laiman and she knew whereof she 
wrote 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
leah laimans life would make a lousy soap opera 
she was raised an orthodox jew in hamilton ontario where she 
spent her weekends reading the classics she moved to new york and 
attended a jewish womens college she did hang around greenwich 
village one summer though she didnt exactly blend into the crowd 
i was the only orthodox kosher virgin beatnik in new york she 
says until her father showed up to take her home 
it is therefore no small irony that laiman a woman with barely 
a nodding acquaintance with lifes seamy side should wind up as the 
head writer for one of the seamier soaps nbcs days of our 
lives 
soap opera digest rated it the most violent soap on television 
bad planning laiman explains murder and mayhem are simply a 
cheap way to end a friday the show did go through a period where 
there was a lot of violence toward women im sorry for that 
other than that though laiman makes no apology for the violence 
and sex served up on her soap sure soap operas are full of sex 
and violence she says but they are not like movies and they 
arent rated r there is a limit to what you can do 
and in a way soaps are very moralistic yes people do naughty 
things but the bad people always get punished the good guys always 
win and get lots of fan mail 
salem usa the shows fictional location is a slightly more 
enlightened place than the whitebread town laiman found when 
she moved over from abcs general hospital three years ago 
like most soap opera settings salem remains overwhelmingly white 
middle class there are two blacks she says and everybodys 
christian 
not quite everyone it turns out 
enter the first orthodox jewish characters in the soap operas 
history 
some people who watch these shows probably dont know any 
jews she explains i just wanted to show they have no horns 
she created robin a beautiful young doctor who just happened to 
be an orthodox jew robin fell in love with mike also a doctor and 
as luck would have it a christian 
robins father was a pharmacist he wore a yarmulke all the 
time robin never ate out in the nonkosher cafeteria at the 
hospital all she could eat was salad 
since intimate dinner dates are a soap opera staple laiman 
created a kosher deli and saw to it robin stayed home on the 
sabbath on friday nights she lit candles and wouldnt answer the 
phone or ride in the car unless it was a medical emergency 
mike gave serious thought to converting then realized he 
couldnt give up his heritage eventually laiman resolved the plot 
by having robin and her father leave town 
laiman regrets that their departure meant there were no more jews 
in salem still the alternatives would have been worse for robin 
to marry a nonjew or worse to abandon her own religion would be 
out of the question 
in charting the soaps plot laiman remains mindful of her 
influence over the audience i would never let a woman have an 
abortion and go crazy about it she says i might not have an 
abortion myself but its not up to me to put that in the show and 
influence people 
after six years in the soap opera business she worked on 
general hospital for three years before moving to days 
laiman says im still shocked to this day that people respond to 
the show the way they do they identify so totally with these 
peoples lives they see them only as these characters 
as head writer laimans job is to map out the story which is 
subject to approval by the network associate head writers break the 
plot down into daily segments dialogue writers fill in the daily 
scripts 
the show is filmed in los angeles but laiman prefers to stay in 
new york she travels to the west coast for meetings but spends 
most of her time in the manhattan apartment she shares with her 
husband producerdirector ralph toporoff her stepdaughter 
melinda 19 and her 15monthold baby danielle the couple also 
has a stepson ian 23 
writing a soap opera doesnt require tremendous writing talent 
though it does require skill and understanding of the medium 
laiman says 
soaps appeal to middleoftheroad conservatives television is 
not about public service its about advertising dollars and ratings 
and not offending viewers 
still she keeps an eye out for ways to incorporate her values 
into the show and to pass along responsible information whenever 
possible 
when the story line dealt with sex abuse laiman included a 
hotline number at the end of the episode she also tried to make 
it very clear that sexual abuse is not the victims fault 
with robins departure salem is for the time being once again 
an allchristian town but laiman says plans are already in the 
works to bring robin back 
in the meantime there are other ways to get her points across 
coming up a love story involving a plastic surgeon who happens to 
be black 
</TEXT>
