<TEXT>
here are some facts and figures on oman 
the land oman lies at the southern end of the persian gulf and 
covers 120000 square miles about the size of new mexico with 
1000 miles of coastline in the strait of hormuz and the indian 
ocean the rocky musamdam peninsula jutting into the strait of 
hormuz is separated from rest of the country by the united arab 
emirates 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the people the omanis are moslem arabs from the qahtan tribes 
that migrated from southern arabia there are also small communities 
of baluchis originally from iran or pakistan and indians the 
people of the musandam are descended from the biblical shihu and 
have their own language 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the economy oman strategically situated between the arab world 
and the orient was a trading center for centuries with links as far 
afield as china oil discovered in 1964 is now the economic 
mainstay although production is a modest 600000 barrels a day oman 
also produces dates and copper camelbreeding is a main crop of the 
inland tribes isolated from the coastal regions by high mountains 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the history after the islamic conquest the portuguese came to 
oman in 1597 but were thrown out by 1650 by 1730 the omanis had 
conquered portuguese settlements in east africa as far south as what 
is now tanzania the british dominated from the second half of the 
19th century until independence in 1951 oman ruled for nearly 250 
years by the albusaid clan was isolated from the outside world for 
decades until 1970 when the britishtrained sultan qaboos bin said 
deposed his father with british jordanian and iranian help he 
crushed a 15year rebellion in dhofar province by the marxist 
popular front for the liberation of oman he revived longdormant 
links with arab states signed a military agreement giving the 
united states base facilities in 1980 and opened diplomatic 
relations with the soviet union in 1985 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

