percent in each of the following two years 
the pay scale at the newspaper currently ranges from 625 a week 
for starting reporters to 895 for reporters with fiveyears 
experience 
union and management initially agreed to a contract on nov 22 
but snags developed over pension formulas and the 250 guild members 
sent their bargainers back to the table 
the negotiators emerged with a second tentative contract shortly 
after a noon strike deadline friday the agreement was nearly 
identical to the first pact but pension benefits were increased by 
6 percent and other minor changes were made 
the night city editors slot will be exempt from union coverage 
and the 500 payment will be made jan 1 instead of july 1 
newsroom employees have been working without a contract since 
june 1 
the suntimes has an estimated circulation of 605000 daily and 
614000 on sunday its competitor chicago tribune has an estimated 
circulation of 765000 daily and 111 million on sunday 
